  • Method Details

    • getTest

      public Method getTest()
      Get the associated test method object of this custom run test. This method can only be called if one test method is specified in the custom run test (Run.test()). Otherwise, use getTest(String).
      Returns:
      the associated test method object.
      Throws:
      TestRunException - if called for a custom run test that specifies multiple test methods in Run.test().

    • getTest

      public Method getTest​(String testName)
      Get the associated method object of the test method with the name testName. This method can only be called if the custom run test specifies more than one test method in (Run.test()). Otherwise, use getTest().
      Parameters:
      testName - the test method for which the method object should be returned.
      Returns:
      the associated test method object with the name testName.
      Throws:
      TestRunException - if there is no test method with the name testName or if called with only one associated test method.

    • isCompilationSkipped

      public boolean isCompilationSkipped()
      Return a boolean indicating if the framework skipped a compilation of the associated test method after the warm-up due to VM flags not allowing a compilation on the requested level in Test.compLevel(). This method can only be called if one test method is specified in the custom run test (Run.test()). Otherwise, use isCompilationSkipped(String).
      Returns:
      true if the framework compiled the test; false otherwise.
      Throws:
      TestRunException - if called for a custom run test that specifies multiple test methods in Run.test().

    • isCompilationSkipped

      public boolean isCompilationSkipped​(String testName)
      Return a boolean indicating if the framework skipped a compilation of the associated test method with the name testName after the warm-up due to VM flags not allowing a compilation on the requested level in Test.compLevel(). This method can only be called if the custom run test specifies more than one test method in (Run.test()). Otherwise, use isCompilationSkipped().
      Parameters:
      testName - the test method for which the method object should be returned.
      Returns:
      true if the framework compiled the test; false otherwise.
      Throws:
      TestRunException - if there is no test method with the name testName or if called with only one associated test method.

    • isTestC1Compiled

      public boolean isTestC1Compiled()
      Returns a boolean indicating if the associated test method is C1 compiled. This method can only be called if one test method is specified in the custom run test (Run.test()). Otherwise, use isTestC1Compiled(String).
      Returns:
      true if the associated test method is C1 compiled; false otherwise.
      Throws:
      TestRunException - if called for a custom run test that specifies multiple test methods in Run.test().

    • isTestC1Compiled

      public boolean isTestC1Compiled​(String testName)

      Parameters:
      testName - the name of the test method.
      Returns:

      Throws:
      TestRunException - if there is no test method with the name testName or if called with only one associated test method.
